<subSubSection lastPageId="177" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="176" pageNumber="177">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="176" pageNumber="177">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 159" captionStartId="F159" captionText="Figure 159. Distribution of Conostegia friedmaniorum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure159" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96517" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">159</figureCitation>
). Endemic to the Caribbean slope of the Cordillera de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tilarán">Tilaran</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Volcán">Volcan</normalizedToken>
Tenorio National Park in Costa Rica, 1250-1700 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="973969" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure159" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96517" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" start="Figure 159" startId="F159">
