Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Almeda &amp; Umana" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia friedmaniorum" order="Myrtales" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="friedmaniorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">Conostegia friedmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph lastPageId="177" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Almeda &amp; Umana" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia friedmaniorum" order="Myrtales" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="friedmaniorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">Conostegia friedmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by its rusty pubescence, leaves which are strongly plinerved with the veins frequently arising in asymmetric fashion, 
<pageBreakToken pageId="177" pageNumber="178" start="start">deflexed</pageBreakToken>
inflorescences and linear-oblong petals. Vegetatively it resembles another Costa Rican endemic, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Umana &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pendula" order="Myrtales" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Conostegia pendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as the Panamanian endemics 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia galdamesiae" order="Myrtales" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galdamesiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Conostegia galdamesiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia papillopetala" order="Myrtales" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillopetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Conostegia papillopetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Umana &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pendula" order="Myrtales" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Conostegia pendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can be distinguished because the latter has lanate indument on the stems which is absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Almeda &amp; Umana" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia friedmaniorum" order="Myrtales" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="friedmaniorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Conostegia friedmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia galdamesiae" order="Myrtales" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galdamesiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Conostegia galdamesiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia papillopetala" order="Myrtales" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillopetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Conostegia papillopetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can be distinguished by its deflexed inflorescence and linear-oblong petals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
